3132 // Calls into the V8 runtime are based on this very simple interface.
3133 // Note: To be able to return two values from some calls the code in
3134 // runtime.cc uses the ObjectPair which is essentially two 32-bit values
3135 // stuffed into a 64-bit value. With the code below we assume that all runtime
3136 // calls return 64 bits of result. If they don't, the a1 result register
3137 // contains a bogus value, which is fine because it is caller-saved.
3138 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3139 using SimulatorRuntimeCall = ObjectPair (*)(
3140 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3141 using SimulatorRuntimeCall = int64_t (*)(
3142 #endif
3143  sreg_t arg0, sreg_t arg1, sreg_t arg2, sreg_t arg3, sreg_t arg4,
3144  sreg_t arg5, sreg_t arg6, sreg_t arg7, sreg_t arg8, sreg_t arg9,
3145  sreg_t arg10, sreg_t arg11, sreg_t arg12, sreg_t arg13, sreg_t arg14,
3146  sreg_t arg15, sreg_t arg16, sreg_t arg17, sreg_t arg18, sreg_t arg19);
3147 
3148 // These prototypes handle the four types of FP calls.
3149 using SimulatorRuntimeCompareCall = int64_t (*)(double darg0, double darg1);
3150 using SimulatorRuntimeFPFPCall = double (*)(double darg0, double darg1);
3151 using SimulatorRuntimeFPCall = double (*)(double darg0);
3152 using SimulatorRuntimeFPIntCall = double (*)(double darg0, int32_t arg0);
3153 using SimulatorRuntimeIntFPCall = int32_t (*)(double darg0);
3154 
3155 // This signature supports direct call in to API function native callback
3156 // (refer to InvocationCallback in v8.h).
3157 using SimulatorRuntimeDirectApiCall = void (*)(sreg_t arg0);
3158 
3159 // This signature supports direct call to accessor getter callback.
3160 using SimulatorRuntimeDirectGetterCall = void (*)(sreg_t arg0, sreg_t arg1);
3161 
3162 // Define four args for future flexibility; at the time of this writing only
3163 // one is ever used.
3164 using SimulatorRuntimeFPTaggedCall = double (*)(int64_t arg0, int64_t arg1,
3165  int64_t arg2, int64_t arg3);
3166 
3167 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3168 using MixedRuntimeCall_0 = AnyCType (*)();
3169 #define BRACKETS(ident, N) ident[N]
3170 #define REP_0(expr, FMT)
3171 #define REP_1(expr, FMT) FMT(expr, 0)
3172 #define REP_2(expr, FMT) REP_1(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 1)
3173 #define REP_3(expr, FMT) REP_2(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 2)
3174 #define REP_4(expr, FMT) REP_3(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 3)
3175 #define REP_5(expr, FMT) REP_4(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 4)
3176 #define REP_6(expr, FMT) REP_5(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 5)
3177 #define REP_7(expr, FMT) REP_6(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 6)
3178 #define REP_8(expr, FMT) REP_7(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 7)
3179 #define REP_9(expr, FMT) REP_8(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 8)
3180 #define REP_10(expr, FMT) REP_9(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 9)
3181 #define REP_11(expr, FMT) REP_10(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 10)
3182 #define REP_12(expr, FMT) REP_11(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 11)
3183 #define REP_13(expr, FMT) REP_12(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 12)
3184 #define REP_14(expr, FMT) REP_13(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 13)
3185 #define REP_15(expr, FMT) REP_14(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 14)
3186 #define REP_16(expr, FMT) REP_15(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 15)
3187 #define REP_17(expr, FMT) REP_16(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 16)
3188 #define REP_18(expr, FMT) REP_17(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 17)
3189 #define REP_19(expr, FMT) REP_18(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 18)
3190 #define REP_20(expr, FMT) REP_19(expr, FMT), FMT(expr, 19)
3191 #define GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT(V) \
3192  V(0) \
3193  V(1) \
3194  V(2) \
3195  V(3) \
3196  V(4) \
3197  V(5) \
3198  V(6) \
3199  V(7) \
3200  V(8) \
3201  V(9) \
3202  V(10) \
3203  V(11) \
3204  V(12) \
3205  V(13) \
3206  V(14) \
3207  V(15) \
3208  V(16) \
3209  V(17) \
3210  V(18) \
3211  V(19) \
3212  V(20)
3213 #define MIXED_RUNTIME_CALL(N) \
3214  using MixedRuntimeCall_##N = AnyCType (*)(REP_##N(AnyCType arg, CONCAT));
3215 GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT(MIXED_RUNTIME_CALL)
3216 #undef MIXED_RUNTIME_CALL
3217 #define CALL_ARGS(N) REP_##N(args, BRACKETS)
3218 #define CALL_TARGET_VARARG(N) \
3219  if (signature.ParameterCount() == N) { /* NOLINT */ \
3220  MixedRuntimeCall_##N target = \
3221  reinterpret_cast<MixedRuntimeCall_##N>(target_address); \
3222  result = target(CALL_ARGS(N)); \
3223  } else /* NOLINT */
3224 #define PARAM_REGISTERS a0, a1, a2, a3, a4, a5, a6, a7
3225 #define RETURN_REGISTER a0
3226 #define FP_PARAM_REGISTERS fa0, fa1, fa2, fa3, fa4, fa5, fa6, fa7
3227 #define FP_RETURN_REGISTER fa0
3228 void Simulator::CallAnyCTypeFunction(Address target_address,
3229  const EncodedCSignature& signature) {
3230  const int64_t* stack_pointer = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(get_register(sp));
3231  const double* double_stack_pointer =
3232  reinterpret_cast<double*>(get_register(sp));
3233  const Register kParamRegisters[] = {PARAM_REGISTERS};
3234  const FPURegister kFPParamRegisters[] = {FP_PARAM_REGISTERS};
3235  CHECK_LE(signature.ParameterCount(), kMaxCParameters);
3236  static_assert(sizeof(AnyCType) == 8, "AnyCType is assumed to be 64-bit.");
3237  AnyCType args[kMaxCParameters];
3238  int num_gp_params = 0, num_fp_params = 0, num_stack_params = 0;
3239  for (int i = 0; i < signature.ParameterCount(); ++i) {
3240  if (signature.IsFloat(i)) {
3241  if (num_fp_params < 8) {
3242  args[i].double_value =
3243  get_fpu_register_double(kFPParamRegisters[num_fp_params++]);
3244  } else {
3245  args[i].double_value = double_stack_pointer[num_stack_params++];
3246  }
3247  } else {
3248  if (num_gp_params < 8) {
3249  args[i].int64_value = get_register(kParamRegisters[num_gp_params++]);
3250  } else {
3251  args[i].int64_value = stack_pointer[num_stack_params++];
3252  }
3253  }
3254  }
3255  AnyCType result;
3256  GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT(CALL_TARGET_VARARG)
3257  /* else */ {
3258  UNREACHABLE();
3259  }
3260  static_assert(20 == kMaxCParameters,
3261  "If you've changed kMaxCParameters, please change the "
3262  "GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT macro.");
3263  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3264  printf("CallAnyCTypeFunction end result \n");
3265  }
3266 #undef CALL_TARGET_VARARG
3267 #undef CALL_ARGS
3268 #undef GEN_MAX_PARAM_COUNT
3269  if (signature.IsReturnFloat()) {
3270  if (signature.IsReturnFloat64()) {
3271  set_fpu_register_double(FP_RETURN_REGISTER, result.double_value);
3272  } else {
3273  set_fpu_register_float(FP_RETURN_REGISTER, result.float_value);
3274  }
3275  } else {
3276  set_register(RETURN_REGISTER, result.int64_value);
3277  }
3278 }
3279 #undef PARAM_REGISTERS
3280 #undef RETURN_REGISTER
3281 #undef FP_PARAM_REGISTERS
3282 #undef FP_RETURN_REGISTER
3283 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3284 
3285 // Software interrupt instructions are used by the simulator to call into the
3286 // C-based V8 runtime. They are also used for debugging with simulator.
3287 void Simulator::SoftwareInterrupt() {
3288  // There are two instructions that could get us here, the ebreak or ecall
3289  // instructions are "SYSTEM" class opcode distinuished by Imm12Value field w/
3290  // the rest of instruction fields being zero
3291  int32_t func = instr_.Imm12Value();
3292  // We first check if we met a call_rt_redirected.
3293  if (instr_.InstructionBits() == rtCallRedirInstr) { // ECALL
3294  Redirection* redirection = Redirection::FromInstruction(instr_.instr());
3295 
3296  // This is dodgy but it works because the C entry stubs are never moved.
3297  int64_t saved_ra = get_register(ra);
3298  intptr_t external =
3299  reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(redirection->external_function());
3300 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3301  Address func_addr =
3302  reinterpret_cast<Address>(redirection->external_function());
3303  SimulatorData* simulator_data = isolate_->simulator_data();
3304  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(simulator_data);
3305  const EncodedCSignature& signature =
3306  simulator_data->GetSignatureForTarget(func_addr);
3307  if (signature.IsValid()) {
3308  CHECK_EQ(redirection->type(), ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL);
3309  CallAnyCTypeFunction(external, signature);
3310  set_register(ra, saved_ra);
3311  set_pc(get_register(ra));
3312  return;
3313  }
3314 #endif
3315 
3316  sreg_t* stack_pointer = reinterpret_cast<sreg_t*>(get_register(sp));
3317 
3318  const sreg_t arg0 = get_register(a0);
3319  const sreg_t arg1 = get_register(a1);
3320  const sreg_t arg2 = get_register(a2);
3321  const sreg_t arg3 = get_register(a3);
3322  const sreg_t arg4 = get_register(a4);
3323  const sreg_t arg5 = get_register(a5);
3324  const sreg_t arg6 = get_register(a6);
3325  const sreg_t arg7 = get_register(a7);
3326  const sreg_t arg8 = stack_pointer[0];
3327  const sreg_t arg9 = stack_pointer[1];
3328  const sreg_t arg10 = stack_pointer[2];
3329  const sreg_t arg11 = stack_pointer[3];
3330  const sreg_t arg12 = stack_pointer[4];
3331  const sreg_t arg13 = stack_pointer[5];
3332  const sreg_t arg14 = stack_pointer[6];
3333  const sreg_t arg15 = stack_pointer[7];
3334  const sreg_t arg16 = stack_pointer[8];
3335  const sreg_t arg17 = stack_pointer[9];
3336  const sreg_t arg18 = stack_pointer[10];
3337  const sreg_t arg19 = stack_pointer[11];
3338  static_assert(kMaxCParameters == 20);
3339 
3340  bool fp_call =
3341  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL) ||
3342  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL) ||
3343  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL) ||
3344  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL) ||
3345  (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL);
3346 
3347  sreg_t pc = get_pc();
3348 
3349  if (fp_call) {
3350  double dval0, dval1; // one or two double parameters
3351  int32_t ival; // zero or one integer parameters
3352  int64_t iresult = 0; // integer return value
3353  double dresult = 0; // double return value
3354  GetFpArgs(&dval0, &dval1, &ival);
3355  SimulatorRuntimeCall generic_target =
3356  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeCall>(external);
3357  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3358  switch (redirection->type()) {
3359  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL:
3360  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL:
3361  PrintF("Call to host function %s at %p with args %f, %f",
3362  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
3363  pc, IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()),
3364  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
3365  dval0, dval1);
3366  break;
3367  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL:
3368  PrintF("Call to host function %s at %p with arg %f",
3369  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
3370  pc, IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()),
3371  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
3372  dval0);
3373  break;
3374  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL:
3375  PrintF("Call to host function %s at %p with args %f, %d",
3376  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
3377  pc, IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()),
3378  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
3379  dval0, ival);
3380  break;
3381  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL:
3382  PrintF("Call to host function %s at %p with args %f",
3383  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
3384  pc, IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()),
3385  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(generic_target)),
3386  dval0);
3387  break;
3388  default:
3389  UNREACHABLE();
3390  }
3391  }
3392  switch (redirection->type()) {
3393  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL: {
3394  SimulatorRuntimeCompareCall target =
3395  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeCompareCall>(external);
3396  iresult = target(dval0, dval1);
3397  set_register(a0, static_cast<sreg_t>(iresult));
3398  // set_register(a1, static_cast<int64_t>(iresult >> 32));
3399  break;
3400  }
3401  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL: {
3402  SimulatorRuntimeFPFPCall target =
3403  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPFPCall>(external);
3404  dresult = target(dval0, dval1);
3405  SetFpResult(dresult);
3406  break;
3407  }
3408  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL: {
3409  SimulatorRuntimeFPCall target =
3410  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPCall>(external);
3411  dresult = target(dval0);
3412  SetFpResult(dresult);
3413  break;
3414  }
3415  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL: {
3416  SimulatorRuntimeFPIntCall target =
3417  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPIntCall>(external);
3418  dresult = target(dval0, ival);
3419  SetFpResult(dresult);
3420  break;
3421  }
3422  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL: {
3423  SimulatorRuntimeIntFPCall target =
3424  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeIntFPCall>(external);
3425  iresult = target(dval0);
3426  set_register(a0, static_cast<int64_t>(iresult));
3427  break;
3428  }
3429  default:
3430  UNREACHABLE();
3431  }
3432  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3433  switch (redirection->type()) {
3434  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL:
3435  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_INT_FP_CALL:
3436  PrintF("Returned %08x\n", static_cast<int32_t>(iresult));
3437  break;
3438  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL:
3439  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_CALL:
3440  case ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL:
3441  PrintF("Returned %f\n", dresult);
3442  break;
3443  default:
3444  UNREACHABLE();
3445  }
3446  }
3447  } else if (redirection->type() ==
3448  ExternalReference::BUILTIN_FP_POINTER_CALL) {
3449  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3450  PrintF("Call to host function at %p args %08" REGIx_FORMAT " \n",
3451  reinterpret_cast<void*>(external), arg0);
3452  }
3453  SimulatorRuntimeFPTaggedCall target =
3454  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeFPTaggedCall>(external);
3455  double dresult = target(arg0, arg1, arg2, arg3);
3456  SetFpResult(dresult);
3457  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3458  PrintF("Returned %f\n", dresult);
3459  }
3460  } else if (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL) {
3461  // See callers of MacroAssembler::CallApiFunctionAndReturn for
3462  // explanation of register usage.
3463  // void f(v8::FunctionCallbackInfo&)
3464  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3465  PrintF("Call to host function %s at %p args %08" REGIx_FORMAT " \n",
3466  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
3467  pc, IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()),
3468  reinterpret_cast<void*>(external), arg0);
3469  }
3470  SimulatorRuntimeDirectApiCall target =
3471  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeDirectApiCall>(external);
3472  target(arg0);
3473  } else if (redirection->type() == ExternalReference::DIRECT_GETTER_CALL) {
3474  // See callers of MacroAssembler::CallApiFunctionAndReturn for
3475  // explanation of register usage.
3476  // void f(v8::Local<String> property, v8::PropertyCallbackInfo& info)
3477  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3478  PrintF("Call to host function at %p args %08" REGIx_FORMAT
3479  " %08" REGIx_FORMAT " \n",
3480  reinterpret_cast<void*>(external), arg0, arg1);
3481  }
3482  SimulatorRuntimeDirectGetterCall target =
3483  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeDirectGetterCall>(external);
3484  target(arg0, arg1);
3485  } else {
3486 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3487  DCHECK(redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_CALL ||
3488  redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_CALL_PAIR);
3489 #else // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3490  // FAST_C_CALL is temporarily handled here as well, because we lack
3491  // proper support for direct C calls with FP params in the simulator.
3492  // The generic BUILTIN_CALL path assumes all parameters are passed in
3493  // the GP registers, thus supporting calling the slow callback without
3494  // crashing. The reason for that is that in the mjsunit tests we check
3495  // the `fast_c_api.supports_fp_params` (which is false on non-simulator
3496  // builds for arm/arm64), thus we expect that the slow path will be
3497  // called. And since the slow path passes the arguments as a `const
3498  // FunctionCallbackInfo<Value>&` (which is a GP argument), the call is
3499  // made correctly.
3500  DCHECK(redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_CALL ||
3501  redirection->type() == ExternalReference::BUILTIN_CALL_PAIR ||
3502  redirection->type() == ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL);
3503 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3504  SimulatorRuntimeCall target =
3505  reinterpret_cast<SimulatorRuntimeCall>(external);
3506  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3507  PrintF(
3508  "Call to host function %s at %p "
3509  "args %08" REGIx_FORMAT " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT
3510  " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT
3511  " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT
3512  " , %08" REGIx_FORMAT " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT
3513  " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT
3514  " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT
3515  " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT " , %016" REGIx_FORMAT " \n",
3516  ExternalReferenceTable::NameOfIsolateIndependentAddress(
3517  pc, IsolateGroup::current()->external_ref_table()),
3518  reinterpret_cast<void*>(FUNCTION_ADDR(target)), arg0, arg1, arg2,
3519  arg3, arg4, arg5, arg6, arg7, arg8, arg9, arg10, arg11, arg12,
3520  arg13, arg14, arg15, arg16, arg17, arg18, arg19);
3521  }
3522 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3523  ObjectPair result = target(arg0, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4, arg5, arg6, arg7,
3524  arg8, arg9, arg10, arg11, arg12, arg13, arg14,
3525  arg15, arg16, arg17, arg18, arg19);
3526  set_register(a0, (sreg_t)(result.x));
3527  set_register(a1, (sreg_t)(result.y));
3528 
3529 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3530  int64_t result = target(arg0, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4, arg5, arg6, arg7,
3531  arg8, arg9, arg10, arg11, arg12, arg13, arg14,
3532  arg15, arg16, arg17, arg18, arg19);
3533  set_register(a0, (sreg_t)result);
3534  set_register(a1, (sreg_t)(result >> 32));
3535 #endif
3536  }
3537  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3538  PrintF("Returned %08" REGIx_FORMAT " : %08" REGIx_FORMAT " \n",
3539  get_register(a1), get_register(a0));
3540  }
3541  set_register(ra, saved_ra);
3542  set_pc(get_register(ra));
3543 
3544  } else if (func == 1) { // EBREAK
3545  int32_t code = get_ebreak_code(instr_.instr());
3546  set_pc(get_pc() + kInstrSize * 2);
3547  if (code != -1 && static_cast<uint32_t>(code) <= kMaxStopCode) {
3548  if (IsWatchpoint(code)) {
3549  PrintWatchpoint(code);
3550  } else if (IsTracepoint(code)) {
3551  if (!v8_flags.debug_sim) {
3552  PrintF("Add --debug-sim when tracepoint instruction is used.\n");
3553  abort();
3554  }
3555  Builtin builtin = LookUp((Address)get_pc());
3556  printf("%d %d %d %d\n", code, code & LOG_TRACE, code & LOG_REGS,
3557  code & kDebuggerTracingDirectivesMask);
3558  if (builtin != Builtin::kNoBuiltinId) {
3559  printf("Builitin: %s\n", builtins_.name(builtin));
3560  }
3561  switch (code & kDebuggerTracingDirectivesMask) {
3562  case TRACE_ENABLE:
3563  if (code & LOG_TRACE) {
3564  v8_flags.trace_sim = true;
3565  }
3566  if (code & LOG_REGS) {
3567  RiscvDebugger dbg(this);
3568  dbg.PrintAllRegs();
3569  }
3570  break;
3571  case TRACE_DISABLE:
3572  if (code & LOG_TRACE) {
3573  v8_flags.trace_sim = false;
3574  }
3575  break;
3576  default:
3577  UNREACHABLE();
3578  }
3579  } else {
3580  IncreaseStopCounter(code);
3581  HandleStop(code);
3582  }
3583  } else if (IsSwitchStackLimit(code)) {
3584  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
3585  PrintF("Switching stack limit\n");
3586  }
3587  DoSwitchStackLimit(instr_.instr());
3588  } else {
3589  // All remaining break_ codes, and all traps are handled here.
3590  RiscvDebugger dbg(this);
3591  dbg.Debug();
3592  }
3593  } else {
3594  UNREACHABLE();
3595  }
3596 }
3597 
3598 // Stop helper functions.
3599 bool Simulator::IsWatchpoint(reg_t code) {
3600  return (code <= kMaxWatchpointCode);
3601 }

3615  " marker: %3d (instr count: %8" PRId64

3622 void Simulator::HandleStop(reg_t code) {
3623  // Stop if it is enabled, otherwise go on jumping over the stop
3624  // and the message address.
3625  if (IsEnabledStop(code)) {
3626  PrintF("Simulator hit stop (%" REGId_FORMAT ")\n", code);
3627  DieOrDebug();
3628  }
3629 }

3631 bool Simulator::IsStopInstruction(Instruction* instr) {
3632  if (instr->InstructionBits() != kBreakInstr) return false;
3633  int32_t code = get_ebreak_code(instr);
3634  return code != -1 && static_cast<uint32_t>(code) > kMaxWatchpointCode &&
3635  static_cast<uint32_t>(code) <= kMaxStopCode;
3636 }

3638 bool Simulator::IsEnabledStop(reg_t code) {
3639  DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
3640  DCHECK_GT(code, kMaxWatchpointCode);
3641  return !(watched_stops_[code].count & kStopDisabledBit);
3642 }
3643 
3644 void Simulator::EnableStop(reg_t code) {
3645  if (!IsEnabledStop(code)) {
3646  watched_stops_[code].count &= ~kStopDisabledBit;
3647  }
3648 }
3649 
3650 void Simulator::DisableStop(reg_t code) {
3651  if (IsEnabledStop(code)) {
3652  watched_stops_[code].count |= kStopDisabledBit;
3653  }
3654 }

3656 void Simulator::IncreaseStopCounter(reg_t code) {
3657  DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
3658  if ((watched_stops_[code].count & ~(1 << 31)) == 0x7FFFFFFF) {
3659  PrintF("Stop counter for code %" REGId_FORMAT
3660  " has overflowed.\n"
3661  "Enabling this code and reseting the counter to 0.\n",
3662  code);
3663  watched_stops_[code].count = 0;
3664  EnableStop(code);
3665  } else {
3666  watched_stops_[code].count++;
3667  }
3668 }
3669 
3670 // Print a stop status.
3671 void Simulator::PrintStopInfo(reg_t code) {
3672  if (code <= kMaxWatchpointCode) {
3673  PrintF("That is a watchpoint, not a stop.\n");
3674  return;
3675  } else if (code > kMaxStopCode) {
3676  PrintF("Code too large, only %u stops can be used\n", kMaxStopCode + 1);
3677  return;
3678  }
3679  const char* state = IsEnabledStop(code) ? "Enabled" : "Disabled";
3680  int32_t count = watched_stops_[code].count & ~kStopDisabledBit;
3681  // Don't print the state of unused breakpoints.
3682  if (count != 0) {
3683  if (watched_stops_[code].desc) {
3684  PrintF("stop %" REGId_FORMAT " - 0x%" REGIx_FORMAT
3685  " : \t%s, \tcounter = %i, \t%s\n",
3686  code, code, state, count, watched_stops_[code].desc);
3687  } else {
3688  PrintF("stop %" REGId_FORMAT " - 0x%" REGIx_FORMAT
3689  " : \t%s, \tcounter = %i\n",
3690  code, code, state, count);
3691  }
3692  }
3693 }
3694 
3695 void Simulator::SignalException(Exception e) {
3696  FATAL("Error: Exception %i raised.", static_cast<int>(e));
3697 }

3699 // RISCV Instruction Decode Routine
3700 void Simulator::DecodeRVRType() {
3701  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kRTypeMask) {
3702  case RO_ADD: {
3703  set_rd(sext_xlen(rs1() + rs2()));
3704  break;
3705  }
3706  case RO_SUB: {
3707  set_rd(sext_xlen(rs1() - rs2()));
3708  break;
3709  }
3710  case RO_SLL: {
3711  set_rd(sext_xlen(rs1() << (rs2() & (xlen - 1))));
3712  break;
3713  }
3714  case RO_SLT: {
3715  set_rd(sreg_t(rs1()) < sreg_t(rs2()));
3716  break;
3717  }
3718  case RO_SLTU: {
3719  set_rd(reg_t(rs1()) < reg_t(rs2()));
3720  break;
3721  }
3722  case RO_XOR: {
3723  set_rd(rs1() ^ rs2());
3724  break;
3725  }
3726  case RO_SRL: {
3727  set_rd(sext_xlen(zext_xlen(rs1()) >> (rs2() & (xlen - 1))));
3728  break;
3729  }
3730  case RO_SRA: {
3731  set_rd(sext_xlen(sext_xlen(rs1()) >> (rs2() & (xlen - 1))));
3732  break;
3733  }
3734  case RO_OR: {
3735  set_rd(rs1() | rs2());
3736  break;
3737  }
3738  case RO_AND: {
3739  set_rd(rs1() & rs2());
3740  break;
3741  }
3742  case RO_ANDN:
3743  set_rd(rs1() & ~rs2());
3744  break;
3745  case RO_ORN:
3746  set_rd(rs1() | (~rs2()));
3747  break;
3748  case RO_XNOR:
3749  set_rd((~rs1()) ^ (~rs2()));
3750  break;
3751 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3752  case RO_ADDW: {
3753  set_rd(sext32(rs1() + rs2()));
3754  break;
3755  }
3756  case RO_ADDUW:
3757  set_rd(zext32(rs1()) + rs2());
3758  break;
3759  case RO_SUBW: {
3760  set_rd(sext32(rs1() - rs2()));
3761  break;
3762  }
3763  case RO_SLLW: {
3764  set_rd(sext32(rs1() << (rs2() & 0x1F)));
3765  break;
3766  }
3767  case RO_SRLW: {
3768  set_rd(sext32(uint32_t(rs1()) >> (rs2() & 0x1F)));
3769  break;
3770  }
3771  case RO_SRAW: {
3772  set_rd(sext32(int32_t(rs1()) >> (rs2() & 0x1F)));
3773  break;
3774  }
3775  case RO_SH1ADDUW: {
3776  set_rd(rs2() + (zext32(rs1()) << 1));
3777  break;
3778  }
3779  case RO_SH2ADDUW: {
3780  set_rd(rs2() + (zext32(rs1()) << 2));
3781  break;
3782  }
3783  case RO_SH3ADDUW: {
3784  set_rd(rs2() + (zext32(rs1()) << 3));
3785  break;
3786  }
3787  case RO_ROLW: {
3788  reg_t extz_rs1 = zext32(rs1());
3789  sreg_t shamt = rs2() & 31;
3790  set_rd(sext32((extz_rs1 << shamt) | (extz_rs1 >> (32 - shamt))));
3791  break;
3792  }
3793  case RO_RORW: {
3794  reg_t extz_rs1 = zext32(rs1());
3795  sreg_t shamt = rs2() & 31;
3796  set_rd(sext32((extz_rs1 >> shamt) | (extz_rs1 << (32 - shamt))));
3797  break;
3798  }
3799 #endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 */
3800  // TODO(riscv): Add RISCV M extension macro
3801  case RO_MUL: {
3802  set_rd(rs1() * rs2());
3803  break;
3804  }
3805  case RO_MULH: {
3806  set_rd(mulh(rs1(), rs2()));
3807  break;
3808  }
3809  case RO_MULHSU: {
3810  set_rd(mulhsu(rs1(), rs2()));
3811  break;
3812  }
3813  case RO_MULHU: {
3814  set_rd(mulhu(rs1(), rs2()));
3815  break;
3816  }
3817  case RO_DIV: {
3818  sreg_t lhs = sext_xlen(rs1());
3819  sreg_t rhs = sext_xlen(rs2());
3820  if (rhs == 0) {
3821  set_rd(-1);
3822  } else if (lhs == INTPTR_MIN && rhs == -1) {
3823  set_rd(lhs);
3824  } else {
3825  set_rd(sext_xlen(lhs / rhs));
3826  }
3827  break;
3828  }
3829  case RO_DIVU: {
3830  reg_t lhs = zext_xlen(rs1());
3831  reg_t rhs = zext_xlen(rs2());
3832  if (rhs == 0) {
3833  set_rd(UINTPTR_MAX);
3834  } else {
3835  set_rd(zext_xlen(lhs / rhs));
3836  }
3837  break;
3838  }
3839  case RO_REM: {
3840  sreg_t lhs = sext_xlen(rs1());
3841  sreg_t rhs = sext_xlen(rs2());
3842  if (rhs == 0) {
3843  set_rd(lhs);
3844  } else if (lhs == INTPTR_MIN && rhs == -1) {
3845  set_rd(0);
3846  } else {
3847  set_rd(sext_xlen(lhs % rhs));
3848  }
3849  break;
3850  }
3851  case RO_REMU: {
3852  reg_t lhs = zext_xlen(rs1());
3853  reg_t rhs = zext_xlen(rs2());
3854  if (rhs == 0) {
3855  set_rd(lhs);
3856  } else {
3857  set_rd(zext_xlen(lhs % rhs));
3858  }
3859  break;
3860  }
3861 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3862  case RO_MULW: {
3863  set_rd(sext32(sext32(rs1()) * sext32(rs2())));
3864  break;
3865  }
3866  case RO_DIVW: {
3867  sreg_t lhs = sext32(rs1());
3868  sreg_t rhs = sext32(rs2());
3869  if (rhs == 0) {
3870  set_rd(-1);
3871  } else if (lhs == INT32_MIN && rhs == -1) {
3872  set_rd(lhs);
3873  } else {
3874  set_rd(sext32(lhs / rhs));
3875  }
3876  break;
3877  }
3878  case RO_DIVUW: {
3879  reg_t lhs = zext32(rs1());
3880  reg_t rhs = zext32(rs2());
3881  if (rhs == 0) {
3882  set_rd(UINT32_MAX);
3883  } else {
3884  set_rd(zext32(lhs / rhs));
3885  }
3886  break;
3887  }
3888  case RO_REMW: {
3889  sreg_t lhs = sext32(rs1());
3890  sreg_t rhs = sext32(rs2());
3891  if (rhs == 0) {
3892  set_rd(lhs);
3893  } else if (lhs == INT32_MIN && rhs == -1) {
3894  set_rd(0);
3895  } else {
3896  set_rd(sext32(lhs % rhs));
3897  }
3898  break;
3899  }
3900  case RO_REMUW: {
3901  reg_t lhs = zext32(rs1());
3902  reg_t rhs = zext32(rs2());
3903  if (rhs == 0) {
3904  set_rd(zext32(lhs));
3905  } else {
3906  set_rd(zext32(lhs % rhs));
3907  }
3908  break;
3909  }
3910 #endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64*/
3911  case RO_SH1ADD:
3912  set_rd(rs2() + (rs1() << 1));
3913  break;
3914  case RO_SH2ADD:
3915  set_rd(rs2() + (rs1() << 2));
3916  break;
3917  case RO_SH3ADD:
3918  set_rd(rs2() + (rs1() << 3));
3919  break;
3920  case RO_MAX:
3921  set_rd(rs1() < rs2() ? rs2() : rs1());
3922  break;
3923  case RO_MAXU:
3924  set_rd(reg_t(rs1()) < reg_t(rs2()) ? rs2() : rs1());
3925  break;
3926  case RO_MIN:
3927  set_rd(rs1() < rs2() ? rs1() : rs2());
3928  break;
3929  case RO_MINU:
3930  set_rd(reg_t(rs1()) < reg_t(rs2()) ? rs1() : rs2());
3931  break;
3932  case RO_ZEXTH:
3933  set_rd(zext_xlen(uint16_t(rs1())));
3934  break;
3935  case RO_ROL: {
3936  sreg_t shamt = rs2() & (xlen - 1);
3937  set_rd((reg_t(rs1()) << shamt) | (reg_t(rs1()) >> (xlen - shamt)));
3938  break;
3939  }
3940  case RO_ROR: {
3941  sreg_t shamt = rs2() & (xlen - 1);
3942  set_rd((reg_t(rs1()) >> shamt) | (reg_t(rs1()) << (xlen - shamt)));
3943  break;
3944  }
3945  case RO_BCLR: {
3946  sreg_t index = rs2() & (xlen - 1);
3947  set_rd(rs1() & ~(1l << index));
3948  break;
3949  }
3950  case RO_BEXT: {
3951  sreg_t index = rs2() & (xlen - 1);
3952  set_rd((rs1() >> index) & 1);
3953  break;
3954  }
3955  case RO_BINV: {
3956  sreg_t index = rs2() & (xlen - 1);
3957  set_rd(rs1() ^ (1 << index));
3958  break;
3959  }
3960  case RO_BSET: {
3961  sreg_t index = rs2() & (xlen - 1);
3962  set_rd(rs1() | (1 << index));
3963  break;
3964  }
3965  case RO_CZERO_EQZ: {
3966  sreg_t condition = rs2();
3967  set_rd(condition == 0 ? 0 : rs1());
3968  break;
3969  }
3970  case RO_CZERO_NEZ: {
3971  sreg_t condition = rs2();
3972  set_rd(condition != 0 ? 0 : rs1());
3973  break;
3974  }
3975  default: {
3976  switch (instr_.BaseOpcode()) {
3977  case AMO:
3978  DecodeRVRAType();
3979  break;
3980  case OP_FP:
3981  DecodeRVRFPType();
3982  break;
3983  default:
3984  UNSUPPORTED();
3985  }
3986  }
3987  }
3988 }

3990 float Simulator::RoundF2FHelper(float input_val, int rmode) {
3991  if (rmode == DYN) rmode = get_dynamic_rounding_mode();
3992 
3993  float rounded = 0;
3994  switch (rmode) {
3995  case RNE: { // Round to Nearest, tiest to Even
3996  rounded = floorf(input_val);
3997  float error = input_val - rounded;
3998 
3999  // Take care of correctly handling the range [-0.5, -0.0], which must
4000  // yield -0.0.
4001  if ((-0.5 <= input_val) && (input_val < 0.0)) {
4002  rounded = -0.0;
4003 
4004  // If the error is greater than 0.5, or is equal to 0.5 and the integer
4005  // result is odd, round up.
4006  } else if ((error > 0.5) ||
4007  ((error == 0.5) && (std::fmod(rounded, 2) != 0))) {
4008  rounded++;
4009  }
4010  break;
4011  }
4012  case RTZ: // Round towards Zero
4013  rounded = std::truncf(input_val);
4014  break;
4015  case RDN: // Round Down (towards -infinity)
4016  rounded = floorf(input_val);
4017  break;
4018  case RUP: // Round Up (towards +infinity)
4019  rounded = ceilf(input_val);
4020  break;
4021  case RMM: // Round to Nearest, tiest to Max Magnitude
4022  rounded = std::roundf(input_val);
4023  break;
4024  default:
4025  UNREACHABLE();
4026  }
4027 
4028  return rounded;
4029 }
4030 
4031 double Simulator::RoundF2FHelper(double input_val, int rmode) {
4032  if (rmode == DYN) rmode = get_dynamic_rounding_mode();
4033 
4034  double rounded = 0;
4035  switch (rmode) {
4036  case RNE: { // Round to Nearest, tiest to Even
4037  rounded = std::floor(input_val);
4038  double error = input_val - rounded;
4039 
4040  // Take care of correctly handling the range [-0.5, -0.0], which must
4041  // yield -0.0.
4042  if ((-0.5 <= input_val) && (input_val < 0.0)) {
4043  rounded = -0.0;
4044 
4045  // If the error is greater than 0.5, or is equal to 0.5 and the integer
4046  // result is odd, round up.
4047  } else if ((error > 0.5) ||
4048  ((error == 0.5) && (std::fmod(rounded, 2) != 0))) {
4049  rounded++;
4050  }
4051  break;
4052  }
4053  case RTZ: // Round towards Zero
4054  rounded = std::trunc(input_val);
4055  break;
4056  case RDN: // Round Down (towards -infinity)
4057  rounded = std::floor(input_val);
4058  break;
4059  case RUP: // Round Up (towards +infinity)
4060  rounded = std::ceil(input_val);
4061  break;
4062  case RMM: // Round to Nearest, tiest to Max Magnitude
4063  rounded = std::round(input_val);
4064  break;
4065  default:
4066  UNREACHABLE();
4067  }
4068  return rounded;
4069 }

4071 // convert rounded floating-point to integer types, handle input values that
4072 // are out-of-range, underflow, or NaN, and set appropriate fflags
4073 template <typename I_TYPE, typename F_TYPE>
4074 I_TYPE Simulator::RoundF2IHelper(F_TYPE original, int rmode) {
4075  DCHECK(std::is_integral_v<I_TYPE>);
4076 
4077  DCHECK((std::is_same_v<F_TYPE, float> || std::is_same_v<F_TYPE, double>));
4078 
4079  I_TYPE max_i = std::numeric_limits<I_TYPE>::max();
4080  I_TYPE min_i = std::numeric_limits<I_TYPE>::min();
4081 
4082  if (!std::isfinite(original)) {
4083  set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4084  if (std::isnan(original) ||
4085  original == std::numeric_limits<F_TYPE>::infinity()) {
4086  return max_i;
4087  } else {
4088  DCHECK(original == -std::numeric_limits<F_TYPE>::infinity());
4089  return min_i;
4090  }
4091  }
4092 
4093  F_TYPE rounded = RoundF2FHelper(original, rmode);
4094  if (original != rounded) set_fflags(kInexact);
4095 
4096  if (!std::isfinite(rounded)) {
4097  set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4098  if (std::isnan(rounded) ||
4099  rounded == std::numeric_limits<F_TYPE>::infinity()) {
4100  return max_i;
4101  } else {
4102  DCHECK(rounded == -std::numeric_limits<F_TYPE>::infinity());
4103  return min_i;
4104  }
4105  }
4106 
4107  // Since integer max values are either all 1s (for unsigned) or all 1s
4108  // except for sign-bit (for signed), they cannot be represented precisely in
4109  // floating point, in order to precisely tell whether the rounded floating
4110  // point is within the max range, we compare against (max_i+1) which would
4111  // have a single 1 w/ many trailing zeros
4112  float max_i_plus_1 =
4113  std::is_same_v<uint64_t, I_TYPE>
4114  ? 0x1p64f // uint64_t::max + 1 cannot be represented in integers,
4115  // so use its float representation directly
4116  : static_cast<float>(static_cast<uint64_t>(max_i) + 1);
4117  if (rounded >= max_i_plus_1) {
4118  set_fflags(kFPUOverflow | kInvalidOperation);
4119  return max_i;
4120  }
4121 
4122  // Since min_i (either 0 for unsigned, or for signed) is represented
4123  // precisely in floating-point, comparing rounded directly against min_i
4124  if (rounded <= min_i) {
4125  if (rounded < min_i) set_fflags(kFPUOverflow | kInvalidOperation);
4126  return min_i;
4127  }
4128 
4129  F_TYPE underflow_fval = std::is_same_v<F_TYPE, float> ? FLT_MIN : DBL_MIN;
4130  if (rounded < underflow_fval && rounded > -underflow_fval && rounded != 0) {
4131  set_fflags(kUnderflow);
4132  }
4133 
4134  return static_cast<I_TYPE>(rounded);
4135 }
4136 
4137 template <typename T>
4138 static int64_t FclassHelper(T value) {
4139  switch (std::fpclassify(value)) {
4140  case FP_INFINITE:
4141  return (std::signbit(value) ? kNegativeInfinity : kPositiveInfinity);
4142  case FP_NAN:
4143  return (isSnan(value) ? kSignalingNaN : kQuietNaN);
4144  case FP_NORMAL:
4145  return (std::signbit(value) ? kNegativeNormalNumber
4146  : kPositiveNormalNumber);
4147  case FP_SUBNORMAL:
4148  return (std::signbit(value) ? kNegativeSubnormalNumber
4149  : kPositiveSubnormalNumber);
4150  case FP_ZERO:
4151  return (std::signbit(value) ? kNegativeZero : kPositiveZero);
4152  default:
4153  UNREACHABLE();
4154  }
4155 }
4156 
4157 template <typename T>
4158 bool Simulator::CompareFHelper(T input1, T input2, FPUCondition cc) {
4159  DCHECK(std::is_floating_point_v<T>);
4160  bool result = false;
4161  switch (cc) {
4162  case LT:
4163  case LE:
4164  // FLT, FLE are signaling compares
4165  if (std::isnan(input1) || std::isnan(input2)) {
4166  set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4167  result = false;
4168  } else {
4169  result = (cc == LT) ? (input1 < input2) : (input1 <= input2);
4170  }
4171  break;
4172 
4173  case EQ:
4174  if (std::numeric_limits<T>::signaling_NaN() == input1 ||
4175  std::numeric_limits<T>::signaling_NaN() == input2) {
4176  set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4177  }
4178  if (std::isnan(input1) || std::isnan(input2)) {
4179  result = false;
4180  } else {
4181  result = (input1 == input2);
4182  }
4183  break;
4184  case NE:
4185  if (std::numeric_limits<T>::signaling_NaN() == input1 ||
4186  std::numeric_limits<T>::signaling_NaN() == input2) {
4187  set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4188  }
4189  if (std::isnan(input1) || std::isnan(input2)) {
4190  result = true;
4191  } else {
4192  result = (input1 != input2);
4193  }
4194  break;
4195  default:
4196  UNREACHABLE();
4197  }
4198  return result;
4199 }

4201 template <typename T>
4202 static inline bool is_invalid_fmul(T src1, T src2) {
4203  return (isinf(src1) && src2 == static_cast<T>(0.0)) ||
4204  (src1 == static_cast<T>(0.0) && isinf(src2));
4205 }
4206 
4207 template <typename T>
4208 static inline bool is_invalid_fadd(T src1, T src2) {
4209  return (isinf(src1) && isinf(src2) &&
4210  std::signbit(src1) != std::signbit(src2));
4211 }
4212 
4213 template <typename T>
4214 static inline bool is_invalid_fsub(T src1, T src2) {
4215  return (isinf(src1) && isinf(src2) &&
4216  std::signbit(src1) == std::signbit(src2));
4217 }
4218 
4219 template <typename T>
4220 static inline bool is_invalid_fdiv(T src1, T src2) {
4221  return ((src1 == 0 && src2 == 0) || (isinf(src1) && isinf(src2)));
4222 }
4223 
4224 template <typename T>
4225 static inline bool is_invalid_fsqrt(T src1) {
4226  return (src1 < 0);
4227 }
4228 
4229 void Simulator::DecodeRVRAType() {
4230  // TODO(riscv): Add macro for RISCV A extension
4231  // Special handling for A extension instructions because it uses func5
4232  // For all A extension instruction, V8 simulator is pure sequential. No
4233  // Memory address lock or other synchronizaiton behaviors.
4234  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kRATypeMask) {
4235  case RO_LR_W: {
4236  sreg_t addr = rs1();
4237  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
4238  {
4239  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&GlobalMonitor::Get()->mutex);
4240  if ((addr & 0x3) != 0) {
4241  DieOrDebug();
4242  }
4243  auto val = ReadMem<int32_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
4244  set_rd(sext32(val), false);
4245  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
4246  local_monitor_.NotifyLoadLinked(addr, TransactionSize::Word);
4247  GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyLoadLinked_Locked(addr,
4248  &global_monitor_thread_);
4249  }
4250  break;
4251  }
4252  case RO_SC_W: {
4253  sreg_t addr = rs1();
4254  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
4255  if ((addr & 0x3) != 0) {
4256  DieOrDebug();
4257  }
4258  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&GlobalMonitor::Get()->mutex);
4259  if (local_monitor_.NotifyStoreConditional(addr, TransactionSize::Word) &&
4260  GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyStoreConditional_Locked(
4261  addr, &global_monitor_thread_)) {
4262  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
4263  GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_thread_);
4264  WriteMem<int32_t>(rs1(), (int32_t)rs2(), instr_.instr());
4265  set_rd(0, false);
4266  } else {
4267  set_rd(1, false);
4268  }
4269  break;
4270  }
4271  case RO_AMOSWAP_W: {
4272  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4273  DieOrDebug();
4274  }
4275  set_rd(sext32(amo<uint32_t>(
4276  rs1(), [&](uint32_t lhs) { return (uint32_t)rs2(); }, instr_.instr(),
4277  WORD)));
4278  break;
4279  }
4280  case RO_AMOADD_W: {
4281  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4282  DieOrDebug();
4283  }
4284  set_rd(sext32(amo<uint32_t>(
4285  rs1(), [&](uint32_t lhs) { return lhs + (uint32_t)rs2(); },
4286  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4287  break;
4288  }
4289  case RO_AMOXOR_W: {
4290  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4291  DieOrDebug();
4292  }
4293  set_rd(sext32(amo<uint32_t>(
4294  rs1(), [&](uint32_t lhs) { return lhs ^ (uint32_t)rs2(); },
4295  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4296  break;
4297  }
4298  case RO_AMOAND_W: {
4299  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4300  DieOrDebug();
4301  }
4302  set_rd(sext32(amo<uint32_t>(
4303  rs1(), [&](uint32_t lhs) { return lhs & (uint32_t)rs2(); },
4304  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4305  break;
4306  }
4307  case RO_AMOOR_W: {
4308  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4309  DieOrDebug();
4310  }
4311  set_rd(sext32(amo<uint32_t>(
4312  rs1(), [&](uint32_t lhs) { return lhs | (uint32_t)rs2(); },
4313  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4314  break;
4315  }
4316  case RO_AMOMIN_W: {
4317  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4318  DieOrDebug();
4319  }
4320  set_rd(sext32(amo<int32_t>(
4321  rs1(), [&](int32_t lhs) { return std::min(lhs, (int32_t)rs2()); },
4322  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4323  break;
4324  }
4325  case RO_AMOMAX_W: {
4326  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4327  DieOrDebug();
4328  }
4329  set_rd(sext32(amo<int32_t>(
4330  rs1(), [&](int32_t lhs) { return std::max(lhs, (int32_t)rs2()); },
4331  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4332  break;
4333  }
4334  case RO_AMOMINU_W: {
4335  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4336  DieOrDebug();
4337  }
4338  set_rd(sext32(amo<uint32_t>(
4339  rs1(), [&](uint32_t lhs) { return std::min(lhs, (uint32_t)rs2()); },
4340  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4341  break;
4342  }
4343  case RO_AMOMAXU_W: {
4344  if ((rs1() & 0x3) != 0) {
4345  DieOrDebug();
4346  }
4347  set_rd(sext32(amo<uint32_t>(
4348  rs1(), [&](uint32_t lhs) { return std::max(lhs, (uint32_t)rs2()); },
4349  instr_.instr(), WORD)));
4350  break;
4351  }
4352 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4353  case RO_LR_D: {
4354  int64_t addr = rs1();
4355  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
4356  {
4357  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&GlobalMonitor::Get()->mutex);
4358  auto val = ReadMem<int64_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
4359  set_rd(val, false);
4360  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
4361  local_monitor_.NotifyLoadLinked(addr, TransactionSize::DoubleWord);
4362  GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyLoadLinked_Locked(addr,
4363  &global_monitor_thread_);
4364  break;
4365  }
4366  }
4367  case RO_SC_D: {
4368  int64_t addr = rs1();
4369  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
4370  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&GlobalMonitor::Get()->mutex);
4371  if (local_monitor_.NotifyStoreConditional(addr,
4372  TransactionSize::DoubleWord) &&
4373  (GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyStoreConditional_Locked(
4374  addr, &global_monitor_thread_))) {
4375  GlobalMonitor::Get()->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_thread_);
4376  WriteMem<int64_t>(rs1(), rs2(), instr_.instr());
4377  set_rd(0, false);
4378  } else {
4379  set_rd(1, false);
4380  }
4381  break;
4382  }
4383  case RO_AMOSWAP_D: {
4384  set_rd(amo<int64_t>(
4385  rs1(), [&](int64_t lhs) { return rs2(); }, instr_.instr(), DWORD));
4386  break;
4387  }
4388  case RO_AMOADD_D: {
4389  set_rd(amo<int64_t>(
4390  rs1(), [&](int64_t lhs) { return lhs + rs2(); }, instr_.instr(),
4391  DWORD));
4392  break;
4393  }
4394  case RO_AMOXOR_D: {
4395  set_rd(amo<int64_t>(
4396  rs1(), [&](int64_t lhs) { return lhs ^ rs2(); }, instr_.instr(),
4397  DWORD));
4398  break;
4399  }
4400  case RO_AMOAND_D: {
4401  set_rd(amo<int64_t>(
4402  rs1(), [&](int64_t lhs) { return lhs & rs2(); }, instr_.instr(),
4403  DWORD));
4404  break;
4405  }
4406  case RO_AMOOR_D: {
4407  set_rd(amo<int64_t>(
4408  rs1(), [&](int64_t lhs) { return lhs | rs2(); }, instr_.instr(),
4409  DWORD));
4410  break;
4411  }
4412  case RO_AMOMIN_D: {
4413  set_rd(amo<int64_t>(
4414  rs1(), [&](int64_t lhs) { return std::min(lhs, rs2()); },
4415  instr_.instr(), DWORD));
4416  break;
4417  }
4418  case RO_AMOMAX_D: {
4419  set_rd(amo<int64_t>(
4420  rs1(), [&](int64_t lhs) { return std::max(lhs, rs2()); },
4421  instr_.instr(), DWORD));
4422  break;
4423  }
4424  case RO_AMOMINU_D: {
4425  set_rd(amo<uint64_t>(
4426  rs1(), [&](uint64_t lhs) { return std::min(lhs, (uint64_t)rs2()); },
4427  instr_.instr(), DWORD));
4428  break;
4429  }
4430  case RO_AMOMAXU_D: {
4431  set_rd(amo<uint64_t>(
4432  rs1(), [&](uint64_t lhs) { return std::max(lhs, (uint64_t)rs2()); },
4433  instr_.instr(), DWORD));
4434  break;
4435  }
4436 #endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64*/
4437  // TODO(riscv): End Add macro for RISCV A extension
4438  default: {
4439  UNSUPPORTED();
4440  }
4441  }
4442 }
4443 
4444 void Simulator::DecodeRVRFPType() {
4445  // OP_FP instructions (F/D) uses func7 first. Some further uses func3 and
4446  // rs2()
4447 
4448  // kRATypeMask is only for func7
4449  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kRFPTypeMask) {
4450  // TODO(riscv): Add macro for RISCV F extension
4451  case RO_FADD_S: {
4452  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4453  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2) {
4454  if (is_invalid_fadd(frs1, frs2)) {
4455  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4456  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4457  } else {
4458  return frs1 + frs2;
4459  }
4460  };
4461  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<float>(fn));
4462  break;
4463  }
4464  case RO_FSUB_S: {
4465  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4466  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2) {
4467  if (is_invalid_fsub(frs1, frs2)) {
4468  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4469  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4470  } else {
4471  return frs1 - frs2;
4472  }
4473  };
4474  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<float>(fn));
4475  break;
4476  }
4477  case RO_FMUL_S: {
4478  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4479  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2) {
4480  if (is_invalid_fmul(frs1, frs2)) {
4481  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4482  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4483  } else {
4484  return frs1 * frs2;
4485  }
4486  };
4487  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<float>(fn));
4488  break;
4489  }
4490  case RO_FDIV_S: {
4491  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4492  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2) {
4493  if (is_invalid_fdiv(frs1, frs2)) {
4494  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4495  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4496  } else if (frs2 == 0.0f) {
4497  this->set_fflags(kDivideByZero);
4498  return (std::signbit(frs1) == std::signbit(frs2)
4499  ? std::numeric_limits<float>::infinity()
4500  : -std::numeric_limits<float>::infinity());
4501  } else {
4502  return frs1 / frs2;
4503  }
4504  };
4505  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<float>(fn));
4506  break;
4507  }
4508  case RO_FSQRT_S: {
4509  if (instr_.Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
4510  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4511  auto fn = [this](float frs) {
4512  if (is_invalid_fsqrt(frs)) {
4513  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4514  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4515  } else {
4516  return std::sqrt(frs);
4517  }
4518  };
4519  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp1<float>(fn));
4520  } else {
4521  UNSUPPORTED();
4522  }
4523  break;
4524  }
4525  case RO_FSGNJ_S: { // RO_FSGNJN_S RO_FSQNJX_S
4526  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4527  case 0b000: { // RO_FSGNJ_S
4528  set_frd(fsgnj32(frs1_boxed(), frs2_boxed(), false, false));
4529  break;
4530  }
4531  case 0b001: { // RO_FSGNJN_S
4532  set_frd(fsgnj32(frs1_boxed(), frs2_boxed(), true, false));
4533  break;
4534  }
4535  case 0b010: { // RO_FSQNJX_S
4536  set_frd(fsgnj32(frs1_boxed(), frs2_boxed(), false, true));
4537  break;
4538  }
4539  default: {
4540  UNSUPPORTED();
4541  }
4542  }
4543  break;
4544  }
4545  case RO_FMIN_S: { // RO_FMAX_S
4546  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4547  case 0b000: { // RO_FMIN_S
4548  set_frd(FMaxMinHelper(frs1(), frs2(), MaxMinKind::kMin));
4549  break;
4550  }
4551  case 0b001: { // RO_FMAX_S
4552  set_frd(FMaxMinHelper(frs1(), frs2(), MaxMinKind::kMax));
4553  break;
4554  }
4555  default: {
4556  UNSUPPORTED();
4557  }
4558  }
4559  break;
4560  }
4561  case RO_FCVT_W_S: { // RO_FCVT_WU_S , 64F RO_FCVT_L_S RO_FCVT_LU_S
4562  float original_val = frs1();
4563  switch (instr_.Rs2Value()) {
4564  case 0b00000: { // RO_FCVT_W_S
4565  set_rd(RoundF2IHelper<int32_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode()));
4566  break;
4567  }
4568  case 0b00001: { // RO_FCVT_WU_S
4569  set_rd(sext32(
4570  RoundF2IHelper<uint32_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode())));
4571  break;
4572  }
4573 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4574  case 0b00010: { // RO_FCVT_L_S
4575  set_rd(RoundF2IHelper<int64_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode()));
4576  break;
4577  }
4578  case 0b00011: { // RO_FCVT_LU_S
4579  set_rd(RoundF2IHelper<uint64_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode()));
4580  break;
4581  }
4582 #endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 */
4583  default: {
4584  UNSUPPORTED();
4585  }
4586  }
4587  break;
4588  }
4589  case RO_FMV_X_W: { // RO_FCLASS_S
4590  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4591  case 0b000: {
4592  if (instr_.Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
4593  // RO_FMV_X_W
4594  set_rd(sext32(get_fpu_register_word(rs1_reg())));
4595  } else {
4596  UNSUPPORTED();
4597  }
4598  break;
4599  }
4600  case 0b001: { // RO_FCLASS_S
4601  set_rd(FclassHelper(frs1()));
4602  break;
4603  }
4604  default: {
4605  UNSUPPORTED();
4606  }
4607  }
4608  break;
4609  }
4610  case RO_FLE_S: { // RO_FEQ_S RO_FLT_S RO_FLE_S
4611  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4612  case 0b010: { // RO_FEQ_S
4613  set_rd(CompareFHelper(frs1(), frs2(), EQ));
4614  break;
4615  }
4616  case 0b001: { // RO_FLT_S
4617  set_rd(CompareFHelper(frs1(), frs2(), LT));
4618  break;
4619  }
4620  case 0b000: { // RO_FLE_S
4621  set_rd(CompareFHelper(frs1(), frs2(), LE));
4622  break;
4623  }
4624  default: {
4625  UNSUPPORTED();
4626  }
4627  }
4628  break;
4629  }
4630  case RO_FCVT_S_W: { // RO_FCVT_S_WU , 64F RO_FCVT_S_L RO_FCVT_S_LU
4631  switch (instr_.Rs2Value()) {
4632  case 0b00000: { // RO_FCVT_S_W
4633  set_frd(static_cast<float>((int32_t)rs1()));
4634  break;
4635  }
4636  case 0b00001: { // RO_FCVT_S_WU
4637  set_frd(static_cast<float>((uint32_t)rs1()));
4638  break;
4639  }
4640 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4641  case 0b00010: { // RO_FCVT_S_L
4642  set_frd(static_cast<float>((int64_t)rs1()));
4643  break;
4644  }
4645  case 0b00011: { // RO_FCVT_S_LU
4646  set_frd(static_cast<float>((uint64_t)rs1()));
4647  break;
4648  }
4649 #endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 */
4650  default: {
4651  UNSUPPORTED();
4652  }
4653  }
4654  break;
4655  }
4656  case RO_FMV_W_X: {
4657  if (instr_.Funct3Value() == 0b000) {
4658  // since FMV preserves source bit-pattern, no need to canonize
4659  Float32 result = Float32::FromBits((uint32_t)rs1());
4660  set_frd(result);
4661  } else {
4662  UNSUPPORTED();
4663  }
4664  break;
4665  }
4666  // TODO(riscv): Add macro for RISCV D extension
4667  case RO_FADD_D: {
4668  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4669  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2) {
4670  if (is_invalid_fadd(drs1, drs2)) {
4671  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4672  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4673  } else {
4674  return drs1 + drs2;
4675  }
4676  };
4677  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<double>(fn));
4678  break;
4679  }
4680  case RO_FSUB_D: {
4681  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4682  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2) {
4683  if (is_invalid_fsub(drs1, drs2)) {
4684  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4685  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4686  } else {
4687  return drs1 - drs2;
4688  }
4689  };
4690  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<double>(fn));
4691  break;
4692  }
4693  case RO_FMUL_D: {
4694  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4695  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2) {
4696  if (is_invalid_fmul(drs1, drs2)) {
4697  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4698  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4699  } else {
4700  return drs1 * drs2;
4701  }
4702  };
4703  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<double>(fn));
4704  break;
4705  }
4706  case RO_FDIV_D: {
4707  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4708  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2) {
4709  if (is_invalid_fdiv(drs1, drs2)) {
4710  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4711  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4712  } else if (drs2 == 0.0) {
4713  this->set_fflags(kDivideByZero);
4714  return (std::signbit(drs1) == std::signbit(drs2)
4715  ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
4716  : -std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity());
4717  } else {
4718  return drs1 / drs2;
4719  }
4720  };
4721  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp2<double>(fn));
4722  break;
4723  }
4724  case RO_FSQRT_D: {
4725  if (instr_.Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
4726  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4727  auto fn = [this](double drs) {
4728  if (is_invalid_fsqrt(drs)) {
4729  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4730  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4731  } else {
4732  return std::sqrt(drs);
4733  }
4734  };
4735  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp1<double>(fn));
4736  } else {
4737  UNSUPPORTED();
4738  }
4739  break;
4740  }
4741  case RO_FSGNJ_D: { // RO_FSGNJN_D RO_FSQNJX_D
4742  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4743  case 0b000: { // RO_FSGNJ_D
4744  set_drd(fsgnj64(drs1_boxed(), drs2_boxed(), false, false));
4745  break;
4746  }
4747  case 0b001: { // RO_FSGNJN_D
4748  set_drd(fsgnj64(drs1_boxed(), drs2_boxed(), true, false));
4749  break;
4750  }
4751  case 0b010: { // RO_FSQNJX_D
4752  set_drd(fsgnj64(drs1_boxed(), drs2_boxed(), false, true));
4753  break;
4754  }
4755  default: {
4756  UNSUPPORTED();
4757  }
4758  }
4759  break;
4760  }
4761  case RO_FMIN_D: { // RO_FMAX_D
4762  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4763  case 0b000: { // RO_FMIN_D
4764  set_drd(FMaxMinHelper(drs1(), drs2(), MaxMinKind::kMin));
4765  break;
4766  }
4767  case 0b001: { // RO_FMAX_D
4768  set_drd(FMaxMinHelper(drs1(), drs2(), MaxMinKind::kMax));
4769  break;
4770  }
4771  default: {
4772  UNSUPPORTED();
4773  }
4774  }
4775  break;
4776  }
4777  case (RO_FCVT_S_D & kRFPTypeMask): {
4778  if (instr_.Rs2Value() == 0b00001) {
4779  auto fn = [](double drs) { return static_cast<float>(drs); };
4780  set_frd(CanonicalizeDoubleToFloatOperation(fn));
4781  } else {
4782  UNSUPPORTED();
4783  }
4784  break;
4785  }
4786  case RO_FCVT_D_S: {
4787  if (instr_.Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
4788  auto fn = [](float frs) { return static_cast<double>(frs); };
4789  set_drd(CanonicalizeFloatToDoubleOperation(fn));
4790  } else {
4791  UNSUPPORTED();
4792  }
4793  break;
4794  }
4795  case RO_FLE_D: { // RO_FEQ_D RO_FLT_D RO_FLE_D
4796  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4797  case 0b010: { // RO_FEQ_S
4798  set_rd(CompareFHelper(drs1(), drs2(), EQ));
4799  break;
4800  }
4801  case 0b001: { // RO_FLT_D
4802  set_rd(CompareFHelper(drs1(), drs2(), LT));
4803  break;
4804  }
4805  case 0b000: { // RO_FLE_D
4806  set_rd(CompareFHelper(drs1(), drs2(), LE));
4807  break;
4808  }
4809  default: {
4810  UNSUPPORTED();
4811  }
4812  }
4813  break;
4814  }
4815  case (RO_FCLASS_D & kRFPTypeMask): { // RO_FCLASS_D , 64D RO_FMV_X_D
4816  if (instr_.Rs2Value() != 0b00000) {
4817  UNSUPPORTED();
4818  }
4819  switch (instr_.Funct3Value()) {
4820  case 0b001: { // RO_FCLASS_D
4821  set_rd(FclassHelper(drs1()));
4822  break;
4823  }
4824 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4825  case 0b000: { // RO_FMV_X_D
4826  set_rd(base::bit_cast<int64_t>(drs1()));
4827  break;
4828  }
4829 #endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 */
4830  default: {
4831  UNSUPPORTED();
4832  }
4833  }
4834  break;
4835  }
4836  case RO_FCVT_W_D: { // RO_FCVT_WU_D , 64F RO_FCVT_L_D RO_FCVT_LU_D
4837  double original_val = drs1();
4838  switch (instr_.Rs2Value()) {
4839  case 0b00000: { // RO_FCVT_W_D
4840  set_rd(RoundF2IHelper<int32_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode()));
4841  break;
4842  }
4843  case 0b00001: { // RO_FCVT_WU_D
4844  set_rd(sext32(
4845  RoundF2IHelper<uint32_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode())));
4846  break;
4847  }
4848 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4849  case 0b00010: { // RO_FCVT_L_D
4850  set_rd(RoundF2IHelper<int64_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode()));
4851  break;
4852  }
4853  case 0b00011: { // RO_FCVT_LU_D
4854  set_rd(RoundF2IHelper<uint64_t>(original_val, instr_.RoundMode()));
4855  break;
4856  }
4857 #endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 */
4858  default: {
4859  UNSUPPORTED();
4860  }
4861  }
4862  break;
4863  }
4864  case RO_FCVT_D_W: { // RO_FCVT_D_WU , 64F RO_FCVT_D_L RO_FCVT_D_LU
4865  switch (instr_.Rs2Value()) {
4866  case 0b00000: { // RO_FCVT_D_W
4867  set_drd((int32_t)rs1());
4868  break;
4869  }
4870  case 0b00001: { // RO_FCVT_D_WU
4871  set_drd((uint32_t)rs1());
4872  break;
4873  }
4874 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4875  case 0b00010: { // RO_FCVT_D_L
4876  set_drd((int64_t)rs1());
4877  break;
4878  }
4879  case 0b00011: { // RO_FCVT_D_LU
4880  set_drd((uint64_t)rs1());
4881  break;
4882  }
4883 #endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 */
4884  default: {
4885  UNSUPPORTED();
4886  }
4887  }
4888  break;
4889  }
4890 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4891  case RO_FMV_D_X: {
4892  if (instr_.Funct3Value() == 0b000 && instr_.Rs2Value() == 0b00000) {
4893  // Since FMV preserves source bit-pattern, no need to canonize
4894  set_drd(base::bit_cast<double>(rs1()));
4895  } else {
4896  UNSUPPORTED();
4897  }
4898  break;
4899  }
4900 #endif /* V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 */
4901  default: {
4902  UNSUPPORTED();
4903  }
4904  }
4905 }
4906 
4907 void Simulator::DecodeRVR4Type() {
4908  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kR4TypeMask) {
4909  // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
4910  case RO_FMADD_S: {
4911  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4912  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2, float frs3) {
4913  if (is_invalid_fmul(frs1, frs2) || is_invalid_fadd(frs1 * frs2, frs3)) {
4914  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4915  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4916  } else {
4917  return std::fma(frs1, frs2, frs3);
4918  }
4919  };
4920  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<float>(fn));
4921  break;
4922  }
4923  case RO_FMSUB_S: {
4924  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4925  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2, float frs3) {
4926  if (is_invalid_fmul(frs1, frs2) || is_invalid_fsub(frs1 * frs2, frs3)) {
4927  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4928  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4929  } else {
4930  return std::fma(frs1, frs2, -frs3);
4931  }
4932  };
4933  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<float>(fn));
4934  break;
4935  }
4936  case RO_FNMSUB_S: {
4937  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4938  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2, float frs3) {
4939  if (is_invalid_fmul(frs1, frs2) || is_invalid_fsub(frs3, frs1 * frs2)) {
4940  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4941  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4942  } else {
4943  return -std::fma(frs1, frs2, -frs3);
4944  }
4945  };
4946  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<float>(fn));
4947  break;
4948  }
4949  case RO_FNMADD_S: {
4950  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4951  auto fn = [this](float frs1, float frs2, float frs3) {
4952  if (is_invalid_fmul(frs1, frs2) || is_invalid_fadd(frs1 * frs2, frs3)) {
4953  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4954  return std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN();
4955  } else {
4956  return -std::fma(frs1, frs2, frs3);
4957  }
4958  };
4959  set_frd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<float>(fn));
4960  break;
4961  }
4962  // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
4963  case RO_FMADD_D: {
4964  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4965  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2, double drs3) {
4966  if (is_invalid_fmul(drs1, drs2) || is_invalid_fadd(drs1 * drs2, drs3)) {
4967  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4968  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4969  } else {
4970  return std::fma(drs1, drs2, drs3);
4971  }
4972  };
4973  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<double>(fn));
4974  break;
4975  }
4976  case RO_FMSUB_D: {
4977  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4978  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2, double drs3) {
4979  if (is_invalid_fmul(drs1, drs2) || is_invalid_fsub(drs1 * drs2, drs3)) {
4980  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4981  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4982  } else {
4983  return std::fma(drs1, drs2, -drs3);
4984  }
4985  };
4986  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<double>(fn));
4987  break;
4988  }
4989  case RO_FNMSUB_D: {
4990  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
4991  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2, double drs3) {
4992  if (is_invalid_fmul(drs1, drs2) || is_invalid_fsub(drs3, drs1 * drs2)) {
4993  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
4994  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4995  } else {
4996  return -std::fma(drs1, drs2, -drs3);
4997  }
4998  };
4999  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<double>(fn));
5000  break;
5001  }
5002  case RO_FNMADD_D: {
5003  // TODO(riscv): use rm value (round mode)
5004  auto fn = [this](double drs1, double drs2, double drs3) {
5005  if (is_invalid_fmul(drs1, drs2) || is_invalid_fadd(drs1 * drs2, drs3)) {
5006  this->set_fflags(kInvalidOperation);
5007  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
5008  } else {
5009  return -std::fma(drs1, drs2, drs3);
5010  }
5011  };
5012  set_drd(CanonicalizeFPUOp3<double>(fn));
5013  break;
5014  }
5015  default:
5016  UNSUPPORTED();
5017  }

5071  RO_V_VLSSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLSSEG7 == instr_temp ||
5072  RO_V_VLSSEG8 == instr_temp) {
5073  UNIMPLEMENTED_RISCV();
5074  return true;
5075  } else if (RO_V_VLXSEG2 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLXSEG3 == instr_temp ||
5076  RO_V_VLXSEG4 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLXSEG5 == instr_temp ||
5077  RO_V_VLXSEG6 == instr_temp || RO_V_VLXSEG7 == instr_temp ||
5078  RO_V_VLXSEG8 == instr_temp) {

5148 
5149 Builtin Simulator::LookUp(Address pc) {
5150  for (Builtin builtin = Builtins::kFirst; builtin <= Builtins::kLast;
5151  ++builtin) {
5152  if (builtins_.code(builtin)->contains(isolate_, pc)) return builtin;
5153  }
5154  return Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
5155 }
5156 
5157 void Simulator::DecodeRVIType() {
5158  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kITypeMask) {
5159  case RO_JALR: {
5160  set_rd(get_pc() + kInstrSize);
5161  // Note: No need to shift 2 for JALR's imm12, but set lowest bit to 0.
5162  sreg_t next_pc = (rs1() + imm12()) & ~sreg_t(1);
5163  set_pc(next_pc);
5164  if (v8_flags.trace_sim) {
5165  Builtin builtin = LookUp((Address)get_pc());
5166  if (builtin != Builtin::kNoBuiltinId) {
5167  auto code = builtins_.code(builtin);
5168  if ((rs1_reg() != ra || imm12() != 0)) {
5169  if ((Address)get_pc() == code->instruction_start()) {
5170  sreg_t arg0 = get_register(a0);
5171  sreg_t arg1 = get_register(a1);
5172  sreg_t arg2 = get_register(a2);
5173  sreg_t arg3 = get_register(a3);
5174  sreg_t arg4 = get_register(a4);
5175  sreg_t arg5 = get_register(a5);
5176  sreg_t arg6 = get_register(a6);
5177  sreg_t arg7 = get_register(a7);
5178  sreg_t* stack_pointer =
5179  reinterpret_cast<sreg_t*>(get_register(sp));
5180  sreg_t arg8 = stack_pointer[0];
5181  sreg_t arg9 = stack_pointer[1];
5182  PrintF(
5183  "Call to Builtin at %s "
5184  "a0 %08" REGIx_FORMAT " ,a1 %08" REGIx_FORMAT
5185  " ,a2 %08" REGIx_FORMAT " ,a3 %08" REGIx_FORMAT
5186  " ,a4 %08" REGIx_FORMAT " ,a5 %08" REGIx_FORMAT
5187  " ,a6 %08" REGIx_FORMAT " ,a7 %08" REGIx_FORMAT
5188  " ,0(sp) %08" REGIx_FORMAT " ,8(sp) %08" REGIx_FORMAT
5189  " ,sp %08" REGIx_FORMAT ",fp %08" REGIx_FORMAT " \n",
5190  builtins_.name(builtin), arg0, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4, arg5,
5191  arg6, arg7, arg8, arg9, get_register(sp), get_register(fp));
5192  }
5193  } else if (rd_reg() == zero_reg) {
5194  PrintF("Return to Builtin at %s \n", builtins_.name(builtin));
5195  }
5196  }
5197  }
5198  break;
5199  }
5200  case RO_LB: {
5201  sreg_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5202  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int8_t))) return;
5203  int8_t val = ReadMem<int8_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5204  set_rd(sext_xlen(val), false);
5205  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
5206  break;
5207  }
5208  case RO_LH: {
5209  sreg_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5210  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int16_t))) return;
5211  int16_t val = ReadMem<int16_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5212  set_rd(sext_xlen(val), false);
5213  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
5214  break;
5215  }
5216  case RO_LW: {
5217  sreg_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5218  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
5219  int32_t val = ReadMem<int32_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5220  set_rd(sext_xlen(val), false);
5221  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
5222  break;
5223  }
5224  case RO_LBU: {
5225  sreg_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5226  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int8_t))) return;
5227  uint8_t val = ReadMem<uint8_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5228  set_rd(zext_xlen(val), false);
5229  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
5230  break;
5231  }
5232  case RO_LHU: {
5233  sreg_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5234  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int16_t))) return;
5235  uint16_t val = ReadMem<uint16_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5236  set_rd(zext_xlen(val), false);
5237  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
5238  break;
5239  }
5240 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5241  case RO_LWU: {
5242  int64_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5243  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int32_t))) return;
5244  uint32_t val = ReadMem<uint32_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5245  set_rd(zext_xlen(val), false);
5246  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
5247  break;
5248  }
5249  case RO_LD: {
5250  int64_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5251  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(int64_t))) return;
5252  int64_t val = ReadMem<int64_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5253  set_rd(sext_xlen(val), false);
5254  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rd_reg()));
5255  break;
5256  }
5257 #endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64*/
5258  case RO_ADDI: {
5259  set_rd(sext_xlen(rs1() + imm12()));
5260  break;
5261  }
5262  case RO_SLTI: {
5263  set_rd(sreg_t(rs1()) < sreg_t(imm12()));
5264  break;
5265  }
5266  case RO_SLTIU: {
5267  set_rd(reg_t(rs1()) < reg_t(imm12()));
5268  break;
5269  }
5270  case RO_XORI: {
5271  set_rd(imm12() ^ rs1());
5272  break;
5273  }
5274  case RO_ORI: {
5275  set_rd(imm12() | rs1());
5276  break;
5277  }
5278  case RO_ANDI: {
5279  set_rd(imm12() & rs1());
5280  break;
5281  }
5282  case OP_SHL: {
5283  switch (instr_.Funct6FieldRaw() | OP_SHL) {
5284  case RO_SLLI:
5285  require(shamt6() < xlen);
5286  set_rd(sext_xlen(rs1() << shamt6()));
5287  break;
5288  case RO_BCLRI: {
5289  require(shamt6() < xlen);
5290  sreg_t index = shamt6() & (xlen - 1);
5291  set_rd(rs1() & ~(1l << index));
5292  break;
5293  }
5294  case RO_BINVI: {
5295  require(shamt6() < xlen);
5296  sreg_t index = shamt6() & (xlen - 1);
5297  set_rd(rs1() ^ (1l << index));
5298  break;
5299  }
5300  case RO_BSETI: {
5301  require(shamt6() < xlen);
5302  sreg_t index = shamt6() & (xlen - 1);
5303  set_rd(rs1() | (1l << index));
5304  break;
5305  }
5306  case OP_COUNT:
5307  switch (instr_.Shamt()) {
5308  case 0: { // clz
5309  sreg_t x = rs1();
5310  int highest_setbit = -1;
5311  for (auto i = xlen - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
5312  if ((x & (1l << i))) {
5313  highest_setbit = i;
5314  break;
5315  }
5316  }
5317  set_rd(xlen - 1 - highest_setbit);
5318  break;
5319  }
5320  case 1: { // ctz
5321  sreg_t x = rs1();
5322  int lowest_setbit = xlen;
5323  for (auto i = 0; i < xlen; i++) {
5324  if ((x & (1l << i))) {
5325  lowest_setbit = i;
5326  break;
5327  }
5328  }
5329  set_rd(lowest_setbit);
5330  break;
5331  }
5332  case 2: { // cpop
5333  int i = 0;
5334  sreg_t n = rs1();
5335  while (n) {
5336  n &= (n - 1);
5337  i++;
5338  }
5339  set_rd(i);
5340  break;
5341  }
5342  case 4:
5343  set_rd(int8_t(rs1()));
5344  break;
5345  case 5:
5346  set_rd(int16_t(rs1()));
5347  break;
5348  default:
5349  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5350  }
5351  break;
5352  default:
5353  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5354  }
5355  break;
5356  }
5357  case OP_SHR: { // RO_SRAI
5358  switch (instr_.Funct6FieldRaw() | OP_SHR) {
5359  case RO_SRLI:
5360  require(shamt6() < xlen);
5361  set_rd(sext_xlen(zext_xlen(rs1()) >> shamt6()));
5362  break;
5363  case RO_SRAI:
5364  require(shamt6() < xlen);
5365  set_rd(sext_xlen(sext_xlen(rs1()) >> shamt6()));
5366  break;
5367  case RO_BEXTI: {
5368  require(shamt6() < xlen);
5369  sreg_t index = shamt6() & (xlen - 1);
5370  set_rd((rs1() >> index) & 1);
5371  break;
5372  }
5373  case RO_ORCB&(kFunct6Mask | OP_SHR): {
5374  reg_t rs1_val = rs1();
5375  reg_t result = 0;
5376  reg_t mask = 0xFF;
5377  reg_t step = 8;
5378  for (reg_t i = 0; i < xlen; i += step) {
5379  if ((rs1_val & mask) != 0) {
5380  result |= mask;
5381  }
5382  mask <<= step;
5383  }
5384  set_rd(result);
5385  break;
5386  }
5387  case RO_RORI: {
5388 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5389  int16_t shamt = shamt6();
5390 #else
5391  int16_t shamt = shamt5();
5392 #endif
5393  set_rd((reg_t(rs1()) >> shamt) | (reg_t(rs1()) << (xlen - shamt)));
5394  break;
5395  }
5396  case RO_REV8: {
5397  if (imm12() == RO_REV8_IMM12) {
5398  reg_t input = rs1();
5399  reg_t output = 0;
5400  reg_t j = xlen - 1;
5401  for (int i = 0; i < xlen; i += 8) {
5402  output |= ((input >> (j - 7)) & 0xff) << i;
5403  j -= 8;
5404  }
5405  set_rd(output);
5406  break;
5407  }
5408  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5409  }
5410  default:
5411  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5412  }
5413  break;
5414  }
5415 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5416  case RO_ADDIW: {
5417  set_rd(sext32(rs1() + imm12()));
5418  break;
5419  }
5420  case OP_SHLW:
5421  switch (instr_.Funct7FieldRaw() | OP_SHLW) {
5422  case RO_SLLIW:
5423  set_rd(sext32(rs1() << shamt5()));
5424  break;
5425  case RO_SLLIUW:
5426  set_rd(zext32(rs1()) << shamt6());
5427  break;
5428  case OP_COUNTW: {
5429  switch (instr_.Shamt()) {
5430  case 0: { // clzw
5431  sreg_t x = rs1();
5432  int highest_setbit = -1;
5433  for (auto i = 31; i >= 0; i--) {
5434  if ((x & (1l << i))) {
5435  highest_setbit = i;
5436  break;
5437  }
5438  }
5439  set_rd(31 - highest_setbit);
5440  break;
5441  }
5442  case 1: { // ctzw
5443  sreg_t x = rs1();
5444  int lowest_setbit = 32;
5445  for (auto i = 0; i < 32; i++) {
5446  if ((x & (1l << i))) {
5447  lowest_setbit = i;
5448  break;
5449  }
5450  }
5451  set_rd(lowest_setbit);
5452  break;
5453  }
5454  case 2: { // cpopw
5455  int i = 0;
5456  int32_t n = static_cast<int32_t>(rs1());
5457  while (n) {
5458  n &= (n - 1);
5459  i++;
5460  }
5461  set_rd(i);
5462  break;
5463  }
5464  default:
5465  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5466  }
5467  break;
5468  }
5469  default:
5470  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5471  }
5472  break;
5473  case OP_SHRW: { // RO_SRAI
5474  switch (instr_.Funct7FieldRaw() | OP_SHRW) {
5475  case RO_SRLIW:
5476  set_rd(sext32(uint32_t(rs1()) >> shamt5()));
5477  break;
5478  case RO_SRAIW:
5479  set_rd(sext32(int32_t(rs1()) >> shamt5()));
5480  break;
5481  case RO_RORIW: {
5482  reg_t extz_rs1 = zext32(rs1());
5483  int16_t shamt = shamt5();
5484  set_rd(sext32((extz_rs1 >> shamt) | (extz_rs1 << (32 - shamt))));
5485  break;
5486  }
5487  default:
5488  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5489  }
5490  break;
5491  }
5492 #endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64*/
5493  case RO_FENCE: {
5494  // DO nothing in sumulator
5495  break;
5496  }
5497  case RO_ECALL: { // RO_EBREAK
5498  if (instr_.Imm12Value() == 0) { // ECALL
5499  SoftwareInterrupt();
5500  } else if (instr_.Imm12Value() == 1) { // EBREAK
5501  SoftwareInterrupt();
5502  } else {
5503  UNSUPPORTED();
5504  }
5505  break;
5506  }
5507  // TODO(riscv): use Zifencei Standard Extension macro block
5508  case RO_FENCE_I: {
5509  // spike: flush icache.
5510  break;
5511  }
5512  // TODO(riscv): use Zicsr Standard Extension macro block
5513  case RO_CSRRW: {
5514  if (rd_reg() != zero_reg) {
5515  set_rd(zext_xlen(read_csr_value(csr_reg())));
5516  }
5517  write_csr_value(csr_reg(), rs1());
5518  break;
5519  }
5520  case RO_CSRRS: {
5521  set_rd(zext_xlen(read_csr_value(csr_reg())));
5522  if (rs1_reg() != zero_reg) {
5523  set_csr_bits(csr_reg(), rs1());
5524  }
5525  break;
5526  }
5527  case RO_CSRRC: {
5528  set_rd(zext_xlen(read_csr_value(csr_reg())));
5529  if (rs1_reg() != zero_reg) {
5530  clear_csr_bits(csr_reg(), rs1());
5531  }
5532  break;
5533  }
5534  case RO_CSRRWI: {
5535  if (rd_reg() != zero_reg) {
5536  set_rd(zext_xlen(read_csr_value(csr_reg())));
5537  }
5538  write_csr_value(csr_reg(), imm5CSR());
5539  break;
5540  }
5541  case RO_CSRRSI: {
5542  set_rd(zext_xlen(read_csr_value(csr_reg())));
5543  if (imm5CSR() != 0) {
5544  set_csr_bits(csr_reg(), imm5CSR());
5545  }
5546  break;
5547  }
5548  case RO_CSRRCI: {
5549  set_rd(zext_xlen(read_csr_value(csr_reg())));
5550  if (imm5CSR() != 0) {
5551  clear_csr_bits(csr_reg(), imm5CSR());
5552  }
5553  break;
5554  }
5555  // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
5556  case RO_FLW: {
5557  sreg_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5558  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(float))) return;
5559  uint32_t val = ReadMem<uint32_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5560  set_frd(Float32::FromBits(val), false);
5561  TraceMemRdFloat(addr, Float32::FromBits(val),
5562  get_fpu_register(frd_reg()));
5563  break;
5564  }
5565  // TODO(riscv): use D Extension macro block
5566  case RO_FLD: {
5567  sreg_t addr = rs1() + imm12();
5568  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, sizeof(double))) return;
5569  uint64_t val = ReadMem<uint64_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5570  set_drd(Float64::FromBits(val), false);
5571  TraceMemRdDouble(addr, Float64::FromBits(val),
5572  get_fpu_register(frd_reg()));
5573  break;
5574  }
5575  default: {
5576 #ifdef CAN_USE_RVV_INSTRUCTIONS
5577  if (!DecodeRvvVL()) {
5578  UNSUPPORTED();
5579  }
5580  break;
5581 #else
5582  UNSUPPORTED();
5583 #endif
5584  }
5585  }
5586 }
5587 
5588 void Simulator::DecodeRVSType() {
5589  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kSTypeMask) {
5590  case RO_SB:
5591  if (!ProbeMemory(rs1() + s_imm12(), sizeof(int8_t))) return;
5592  WriteMem<uint8_t>(rs1() + s_imm12(), (uint8_t)rs2(), instr_.instr());
5593  break;
5594  case RO_SH:
5595  if (!ProbeMemory(rs1() + s_imm12(), sizeof(int16_t))) return;
5596  WriteMem<uint16_t>(rs1() + s_imm12(), (uint16_t)rs2(), instr_.instr());
5597  break;
5598  case RO_SW:
5599  if (!ProbeMemory(rs1() + s_imm12(), sizeof(int32_t))) return;
5600  WriteMem<uint32_t>(rs1() + s_imm12(), (uint32_t)rs2(), instr_.instr());
5601  break;
5602 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5603  case RO_SD:
5604  if (!ProbeMemory(rs1() + s_imm12(), sizeof(int64_t))) return;
5605  WriteMem<uint64_t>(rs1() + s_imm12(), (uint64_t)rs2(), instr_.instr());
5606  break;
5607 #endif /*V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64*/
5608  // TODO(riscv): use F Extension macro block
5609  case RO_FSW: {
5610  if (!ProbeMemory(rs1() + s_imm12(), sizeof(float))) return;
5611  WriteMem<Float32>(rs1() + s_imm12(),
5612  get_fpu_register_Float32(rs2_reg(), false),
5613  instr_.instr());
5614  break;
5615  }
5616  // TODO(riscv): use D Extension macro block
5617  case RO_FSD: {
5618  if (!ProbeMemory(rs1() + s_imm12(), sizeof(double))) return;
5619  WriteMem<Float64>(rs1() + s_imm12(), get_fpu_register_Float64(rs2_reg()),
5620  instr_.instr());
5621  break;
5622  }
5623  default:
5624 #ifdef CAN_USE_RVV_INSTRUCTIONS
5625  if (!DecodeRvvVS()) {
5626  UNSUPPORTED();
5627  }
5628  break;
5629 #else
5630  UNSUPPORTED();
5631 #endif
5632  }
5633 }
5634 
5635 void Simulator::DecodeRVBType() {
5636  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kBTypeMask) {
5637  case RO_BEQ:
5638  if (rs1() == rs2()) {
5639  int64_t next_pc = get_pc() + boffset();
5640  set_pc(next_pc);
5641  }
5642  break;
5643  case RO_BNE:
5644  if (rs1() != rs2()) {
5645  int64_t next_pc = get_pc() + boffset();
5646  set_pc(next_pc);
5647  }
5648  break;
5649  case RO_BLT:
5650  if (rs1() < rs2()) {
5651  int64_t next_pc = get_pc() + boffset();
5652  set_pc(next_pc);
5653  }
5654  break;
5655  case RO_BGE:
5656  if (rs1() >= rs2()) {
5657  int64_t next_pc = get_pc() + boffset();
5658  set_pc(next_pc);
5659  }
5660  break;
5661  case RO_BLTU:
5662  if ((reg_t)rs1() < (reg_t)rs2()) {
5663  int64_t next_pc = get_pc() + boffset();
5664  set_pc(next_pc);
5665  }
5666  break;
5667  case RO_BGEU:
5668  if ((reg_t)rs1() >= (reg_t)rs2()) {
5669  int64_t next_pc = get_pc() + boffset();
5670  set_pc(next_pc);
5671  }
5672  break;
5673  default:
5674  UNSUPPORTED();
5675  }
5676 }
5677 void Simulator::DecodeRVUType() {
5678  // U Type doesn't have additoinal mask
5679  switch (instr_.BaseOpcodeFieldRaw()) {
5680  case LUI:
5681  set_rd(u_imm20());
5682  break;
5683  case AUIPC:
5684  set_rd(sext_xlen(u_imm20() + get_pc()));
5685  break;
5686  default:
5687  UNSUPPORTED();
5688  }
5689 }
5690 void Simulator::DecodeRVJType() {
5691  // J Type doesn't have additional mask
5692  switch (instr_.BaseOpcodeValue()) {
5693  case JAL: {
5694  set_rd(get_pc() + kInstrSize);
5695  int64_t next_pc = get_pc() + imm20J();
5696  set_pc(next_pc);
5697  break;
5698  }
5699  default:
5700  UNSUPPORTED();
5701  }
5702 }
5703 void Simulator::DecodeCRType() {
5704  switch (instr_.RvcFunct4Value()) {
5705  case 0b1000:
5706  if (instr_.RvcRs1Value() != 0 && instr_.RvcRs2Value() == 0) { // c.jr
5707  set_pc(rvc_rs1());
5708  } else if (instr_.RvcRdValue() != 0 &&
5709  instr_.RvcRs2Value() != 0) { // c.mv
5710  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(rvc_rs2()));
5711  } else {
5712  UNSUPPORTED_RISCV();
5713  }
5714  break;
5715  case 0b1001:
5716  if (instr_.RvcRs1Value() == 0 && instr_.RvcRs2Value() == 0) { // c.ebreak
5717  DieOrDebug();
5718  } else if (instr_.RvcRdValue() != 0 &&
5719  instr_.RvcRs2Value() == 0) { // c.jalr
5720  set_register(ra, get_pc() + kShortInstrSize);
5721  set_pc(rvc_rs1());
5722  } else if (instr_.RvcRdValue() != 0 &&
5723  instr_.RvcRs2Value() != 0) { // c.add
5724  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(rvc_rs1() + rvc_rs2()));
5725  } else {
5726  UNSUPPORTED();
5727  }
5728  break;
5729  default:
5730  UNSUPPORTED();
5731  }
5732 }
5733 
5734 void Simulator::DecodeCAType() {
5735  switch (instr_.InstructionBits() & kCATypeMask) {
5736  case RO_C_SUB:
5737  set_rvc_rs1s(sext_xlen(rvc_rs1s() - rvc_rs2s()));
5738  break;
5739  case RO_C_XOR:
5740  set_rvc_rs1s(rvc_rs1s() ^ rvc_rs2s());
5741  break;
5742  case RO_C_OR:
5743  set_rvc_rs1s(rvc_rs1s() | rvc_rs2s());
5744  break;
5745  case RO_C_AND:
5746  set_rvc_rs1s(rvc_rs1s() & rvc_rs2s());
5747  break;
5748 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5749  case RO_C_SUBW:
5750  set_rvc_rs1s(sext32(rvc_rs1s() - rvc_rs2s()));
5751  break;
5752  case RO_C_ADDW:
5753  set_rvc_rs1s(sext32(rvc_rs1s() + rvc_rs2s()));
5754  break;
5755 #endif
5756  default:
5757  UNSUPPORTED();
5758  }
5759 }

5761 void Simulator::DecodeCIType() {
5762  switch (instr_.RvcOpcode()) {
5763  case RO_C_NOP_ADDI:
5764  if (instr_.RvcRdValue() == 0) // c.nop
5765  break;
5766  else // c.addi
5767  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(rvc_rs1() + rvc_imm6()));
5768  break;
5769 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5770  case RO_C_ADDIW:
5771  set_rvc_rd(sext32(rvc_rs1() + rvc_imm6()));
5772  break;
5773 #endif
5774  case RO_C_LI:
5775  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(rvc_imm6()));
5776  break;
5777  case RO_C_LUI_ADD:
5778  if (instr_.RvcRdValue() == 2) {
5779  // c.addi16sp
5780  int64_t value = get_register(sp) + rvc_imm6_addi16sp();
5781  set_register(sp, value);
5782  } else if (instr_.RvcRdValue() != 0 && instr_.RvcRdValue() != 2) {
5783  // c.lui
5784  set_rvc_rd(rvc_u_imm6());
5785  } else {
5786  UNSUPPORTED();
5787  }
5788  break;
5789  case RO_C_SLLI:
5790  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(rvc_rs1() << rvc_shamt6()));
5791  break;
5792  case RO_C_FLDSP: {
5793  sreg_t addr = get_register(sp) + rvc_imm6_ldsp();
5794  uint64_t val = ReadMem<uint64_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5795  set_rvc_drd(Float64::FromBits(val), false);
5796  TraceMemRdDouble(addr, Float64::FromBits(val),
5797  get_fpu_register(rvc_frd_reg()));
5798  break;
5799  }
5800 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5801  case RO_C_LWSP: {
5802  sreg_t addr = get_register(sp) + rvc_imm6_lwsp();
5803  int64_t val = ReadMem<int32_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5804  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(val), false);
5805  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rvc_rd_reg()));
5806  break;
5807  }
5808  case RO_C_LDSP: {
5809  sreg_t addr = get_register(sp) + rvc_imm6_ldsp();
5810  int64_t val = ReadMem<int64_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5811  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(val), false);
5812  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rvc_rd_reg()));
5813  break;
5814  }
5815 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5816  case RO_C_FLWSP: {
5817  sreg_t addr = get_register(sp) + rvc_imm6_ldsp();
5818  uint32_t val = ReadMem<uint32_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5819  set_rvc_frd(Float32::FromBits(val), false);
5820  TraceMemRdFloat(addr, Float32::FromBits(val),
5821  get_fpu_register(rvc_frd_reg()));
5822  break;
5823  }
5824  case RO_C_LWSP: {
5825  sreg_t addr = get_register(sp) + rvc_imm6_lwsp();
5826  int32_t val = ReadMem<int32_t>(addr, instr_.instr());
5827  set_rvc_rd(sext_xlen(val), false);
5828  TraceMemRd(addr, val, get_register(rvc_rd_reg()));
5829  break;
5830  }
5831 #endif
5832  default:
5833  UNSUPPORTED();
5834  }
5835 }

5841  break;
